    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In connection with my No. 28.of the 9th instant I
                    inclose herewith a copy of a letter from the Secretary of the Navy, dated the
                    10th instant, announcing that the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Pensacola</hi> has
                    been directed to proceed to Honolulu, and to remain there until further
                    ordered.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="1184" n="1178" xml:id="pg_1178"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 29.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tracy</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1891</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge, with thanks,
                        the receipt of your letter of the 9th instant, inclosing copy of a dispatch
                        from the United States minister to Hawaii, presenting the necessity of an
                        American man-of-war at Honolulu, and to inform you that the U. S. S. <hi
                            rend="italic">Pensacola</hi> was directed by telegram, on the 7th
                        instant to proceed to Honolulu and to remain there until further
                        instructed.</p>
                    <p>Very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">B. F. Tracy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Secretary of the Navy.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
